    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-09-02T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-09-02T00:00:00-05:00" n="790"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d790">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">751R.62114/8–1944</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        British Ambassador</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Halifax</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <p>The Secretary of State presents his compliments to His Excellency the British
                    Ambassador and has the honor to refer to the Embassy’s note No. 526, Reference:
                    2609/24/44, dated August 19, 1944, concerning the proposal for a governmental
                    statement in connection with the shooting of German prisoners by the French
                    Forces of the Interior in retaliation for the execution of patriot French
                    prisoners by the Germans.</p>
                <p>The Government of the United States concurs in the position taken by the British
                    Government and prefers to make no further public statement with regard to this
                    matter.</p>
                <closer>
                    <dateline rendition="#left">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-09-02">September 2,
                            1944</date>.</dateline>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
